On Military Spouse Day, President Donald Trump issued a proclamation honoring military spouses for their contributions to the defense of the United States. The proclamation recognizes the sacrifices and service of military spouses who support their partners in the military. It acknowledges the challenges they face, such as frequent relocations and managing households alone during deployments. The president also calls on American businesses to create opportunities for hiring and promoting military spouses, emphasizing their valuable skills and experiences. The proclamation concludes by urging the American people to honor military spouses through appropriate ceremonies and activities.